listOfEpisodes.episodePlot: Undercurrents of passion, greed, jealousy and intrigue surface in a seemingly respectable town when a high school homecoming queen is found murdered.
Cooper makes a connection with Audrey Horne and interrogates James. Ed reveals his beer had probably been drugged at the Roadhouse. Mrs. Palmer has a terrible vision.
Dale demonstrates odd deductive techniques for the sheriff's department; Benjamin and his brother take a trip; and Donna and James plan to solve Laura's murder.
The people of Twin Peaks gather for Laura Palmer's funeral. Agent Cooper interprets his dream about the killer. Truman reveals to Cooper the secret of the Bookhouse Boys.

Cooper and Truman track down the one-armed man and some strange new evidence in Laura Palmer's murder. Norma Jennings goes to a parole board hearing for her husband. Audrey Horne decides to begin her own investigation.
Cooper and Truman discover evidence in the woods related to the death of Laura Palmer.
The Bookhouse Boys visit One Eyed Jacks across the border in Canada to find Jacques Renault.
Ben Horne's plans are finally realized, with unforeseen consequences.
In the aftermath of the incident at the Great Northern Hotel, the investigation into Laura Palmer's death continues, and information is provided from an unexpected source.
Agent Cooper receives unwanted help and unwelcome news, and Audrey gets into deeper trouble.
Cooper and Truman discover an unexpected twist in the trail of Laura Palmer's murderer.
Ben Horne asks Cooper for help in rescuing Audrey, and Donna uncovers a significant piece of evidence at Harold Smith's home.
Donna, after discovering that Harold has Laura's secret diary, hatches a risky plan with Maddy to steal it from his home.
Cooper and Truman raid One Eye Jack's, and Shelly and Bobby host a welcome home party for Leo.
Maddy prepares to leave Twin Peaks, Pete uncovers the truth behind Tojamura's intentions, and Cooper receives a devastating message.
Ben receives an unwelcome surprise; Norma's mother arrives in Twin Peaks with a new husband; and Bob covers his tracks.
Cooper attempts to locate Laura's killer after the discovery of another victim.
Blaming Cooper for the death of his brother, Jean Renault plots his revenge as the eccentric FBI agent prepares to leave Twin Peaks.
Sheriff Truman defends Agent Cooper's activities at One Eyed Jack's when they come under scrutiny.
Cooper finds a clue, while Dick Tremayne and Andy confront concerns over Little Nicky's past.
Agent Cooper and Sheriff Truman arrange a trap for Jean Renault.
Cooper reveals the history of Windom Earle to Truman, and Audrey strikes a deal with Bobby.
Agent Cooper finds out who shot him and gets help with his deadly chess game against Windom Earle.
While Cooper and Earle plot their next moves, Josie is forced to meet with Thomas Eckhardt.
Cooper is attracted to a beautiful, reclusive woman as Truman grieves over Josie's death.
Cooper and the officers look into Windom Earle's past, and Donna observes a suspicious encounter between her mother and Ben Horne.
While Cooper and Truman try to unlock the secret of Owl Cave, the Miss Twin Peaks contest draws hot competition.
While romance blooms for Cooper and Annie, Donna finds a scrapbook that's full of surprises.
Agent Cooper and Sheriff Truman rush to the Black Lodge, where Cooper tries to save the life of Miss Twin Peaks.
Cooper must overcome his deepest fears as he enters the Black Lodge to save Annie from Windom Earle.

name: Twin Peaks
plot: An idiosyncratic FBI agent investigates the murder of a young woman in the even more idiosyncratic town of Twin Peaks.
